      "text/plain": [
       "estimate_pi (generic function with 1 method)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 49,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "function estimate_pi(num_points)\n",
    "    points_inside_circle = 0\n",
    "\n",
    "    for _ in 1:num_points\n",
    "        x, y = rand(), rand()\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Check if the point is inside the unit circle (quarter circle)\n",
    "        if x^2 + y^2 <= 1.0\n",
    "            points_inside_circle += 1\n",
    "        end\n",
    "    end\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Estimate π using the ratio of points inside the circle to total points\n",
    "    estimated_pi = 4 * points_inside_circle / num_points\n",
    "\n",
    "    return estimated_pi\n",
    "end"
   ]
  },
  {

   "execution_count": 50,
   "id": "c6a21f88",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "estimate_pi_with_plot (generic function with 1 method)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 50,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "function estimate_pi_with_plot(num_points)\n",
    "    points_inside_circle = 0\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Arrays to store coordinates of points inside and outside the circle\n",
    "    x_inside, y_inside = Float64[], Float64[]\n",
    "    x_outside, y_outside = Float64[], Float64[]\n",
    "\n",
    "    for _ in 1:num_points\n",
    "        x, y = rand(), rand()\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Check if the point is inside the unit circle (quarter circle)\n",
    "        if x^2 + y^2 <= 1.0\n",
    "            points_inside_circle += 1\n",
    "            push!(x_inside, x)\n",
    "            push!(y_inside, y)\n",
    "        else\n",
    "            push!(x_outside, x)\n",
    "            push!(y_outside, y)\n",
    "        end\n",
    "    end\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Estimate π using the ratio of points inside the circle to total points\n",
    "    estimated_pi = 4 * points_inside_circle / num_points\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "    return estimated_pi, x_inside, y_inside, x_outside, y_outside\n",
    "\n",
    "end"
   ]
  },

    "# Set the number of random points to generate\n",
    "num_points = 10000\n",
    "\n",
    "# Calculate the estimated value of π and plot the results\n",
    "result, x_inside, y_inside, x_outside, y_outside = estimate_pi_with_plot(num_points)\n",
    "\n",
    "println(\"Estimated value of π using Monte Carlo: \", result)"
